TI  == characterization of the rnd-type multidrug efflux pump mexab-oprm of the plant pathogen pseudomonas syringae.
AB  == in gram-negative bacteria, transporters belonging to the rnd family are the transporters most relevant for resistance to antimicrobial compounds. in pseudomonas aeruginosa, a clinically important pathogen, the rnd-type pump mexab-oprm has been recognized as one of the major multidrug efflux systems. here, homologues of mexab-oprm in the plant pathogens pseudomonas syringae pv. phaseolicola 1448a, p. syringae pv. syringae b728a, and p. syringae pv. tomato dc3000 were identified, and mexab-oprm-deficient mutants were generated. determination of mics revealed that mutation of mexab-oprm dramatically reduced the tolerance to a broad range of antimicrobials. moreover, the ability of the mexab-oprm-deficient mutants to multiply in planta was reduced. rna dot blot hybridization revealed growth-dependent regulation of the mexab-oprm operon in p. syringae; the expression of this operon was maximal in early exponential phase and decreased gradually during further growth.
